==English==

===Etymology===
The term dates from the 1960s or earlier, a hybrid of the Greek [[poly]] for [[many]] and the Latin [[amor]] for [[love]].

===Noun===
'''polyamory'''

# Any of various practices involving [[relationship]]s with multiple [[partner]]s with the knowledge and consent of all involved.

